A surprisingly interesting set of questions. It was hard to answer without context, for example, Michelle could have been entirely sincere or entirely insincere in the question about the film. We don't know her motivation for answering as she did, or her relationship to the questioner which might influence her response. Similarly, rating oneself was difficult. For example, I am knowledgable about some things but not about others, does that make me ignorant or not? I would have liked an 'it depends' option!

some of the questions were difficult to answer without context. For example, the impact of a money on a struggling business very much depends on the size of the business!

The questions that repeat "Did you think about the impact of....x" must have been affected by repetition - as it became evident that each scenario was going to ask that question, then I *did* start to think about the impact in advance more than I did for the first one.  But maybe that was intentional?

"do you think what would have happened..." which was a question asked several times with the scenarios doesn't make sense (possibly a typing error - should it have meant "do you think that would have happened?"?). The error could cause confusion, meaning that the responses may not have all been accurate. 

Overall, enjoyable study.
